# Visual Stability: Localized Error Boundaries

- Wrap isolated widgets and complex async views in localized error boundaries.
- A failure in one data stream must degrade gracefully without crashing the surrounding page.
- Provide contextual fallback UI with a retry action where recovery is possible.
- Do NOT route non-fatal widget errors into app-wide fatal boundaries.

## Example

```tsx
// Good: failure is contained to one section
<WidgetErrorBoundary fallback={<RevenueWidgetFallback />}>
  <RevenueWidget />
</WidgetErrorBoundary>
```
